{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5cddfccf-1ccc-40b2-8c24-96da6ad776d8","content":"I don't see a `.dmp` file in the current directory, and `dotnet-dump` isn't installed yet. Here's what I need from you:\n\n1. **Where is the dump file?** — Provide the full path to the `.dmp` file.\n2. **What .NET version?** — .NET 6/7/8/9 or .NET Framework?\n3. **What OS was the dump captured on?** — Windows or Linux?\n\nIn the meantime, here's how to analyze it once we have the file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (recommended for .NET Core/.NET 5+):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-dump.dmp>\n```\n\nKey commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` | Print last exception (crash cause) |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrstack -all` | All managed thread stacks |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (OOM diagnosis) |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n\n**Typical workflow:**\n```\n> pe                   # See the exception that caused the crash\n> clrstack             # See where it happened\n> clrstack -all        # Check all threads for deadlocks/issues\n```\n\nLet me know the file path and I can walk you through the analysis interactively!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"71c8926f-14aa-40de-845f-18f126769558","outputTokens":361},"id":"33ef7475-320b-4f45-b5b9-305974ebbfc8","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:09:49.477Z","parentId":"4c8f9259-32e1-4d3b-9cc7-450ef5ff6278"}
